title: How to Bake Peach Muffins

text: Preheat oven to 200ºC/400ºF. Lightly grease 16 muffin cups. In a large bowl, mix the flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt. In a separate bowl, mix the oil, sugar and eggs. Stir the oil mixture into the flour mixture just until moist. Fold in the peaches. Spoon into the prepared muffin cups. Bake for 25 minutes in the preheated oven, until a toothpick inserted in the centre of the muffins comes out clean.  Cool for 10 minutes until putting the muffins on a wire rack to cool completely.
